# WHAT IT IS
#   CommandKit is "the discord.js meta-framework with features such
#   as AI-powered command handler, file-based routing, hot module
#   replacement, ratelimit, cache, queue, analytics, devtools,
#   workflow engine, JSX components, and more".  It plays the same
#   role for Discord bots that Next.js plays for React websites —
#   it provides a CLI (`commandkit`) that bootstraps `dev` (with
#   HMR), `build` (production bundle), `start` (production
#   runtime), `typegen` (typed-command declaration generation),
#   `create` (file scaffolder for commands / events / plugin
#   templates), and `info` (debug environment report).  The
#   framework wraps `discord.js` (declared as a `catalog:` peer
#   dependency) with a file-based command/event router, an HMR
#   reload loop, plugin system, and a hooks API for AI-driven
#   command handlers.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from packages/commandkit/src/
#                       cli/init.ts `bootstrapCommandkitCLI` —
#                       Commander v14 with `Command` chain)
#   commandkit <SUBCOMMAND> [options...]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     dev                            Start your bot in development
#                                    mode (HMR-enabled)
#       -c, --config [PATH]            Path to commandkit config
#                                      [default: ./commandkit.js]
#
#     start                          Start your bot in production
#                                    mode (run after `build`)
#       -c, --config [PATH]            Path to commandkit config
#
#     build                          Build the project for
#                                    production
#       -c, --config [PATH]            Path to commandkit config
#
#     typegen                        Generate typed command
#                                    declarations from the
#                                    commands router
#       -c, --config [PATH]            Path to commandkit config
#
#     create <TEMPLATE> [args...]    Create new files from a
#                                    built-in or plugin template
#       Built-in templates:
#         command <NAME>               Scaffold a command file
#         event <NAME>                 Scaffold an event handler
#       Plus any plugin-registered template via the compiler
#       plugin runtime.
#
#     info                           Show environment info (Node
#                                    version, OS, package
#                                    versions) useful for bug
#                                    reports
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `discord.js` (declared at workspace-
#   catalog level `catalog:discordjs`, with consumer
#   applications installing the canonical npm `discord.js`
#   package).  `discord.js` is THE canonical Node.js Discord
#   library maintained by the discordjs org (discordjs/
#   discord.js, 25K+ stars, the Node counterpart of serenity-rs
#   / discordgo / discord.py).  discord.js exposes the
#   `Client`, `IntentsBitField`, `GatewayIntentBits`,
#   `Partials`, `Events`, the typed `Message`, `Interaction`,
#   `ButtonInteraction`, `StringSelectMenuInteraction`,
#   `ModalSubmitInteraction`, `AutocompleteInteraction`,
#   `Guild`, `GuildMember`, `Channel`, `TextChannel`,
#   `VoiceChannel`, `ThreadChannel`, `User`, `Role`,
#   `MessageEmbed` / `EmbedBuilder`, `ActionRowBuilder`,
#   `ButtonBuilder`, `StringSelectMenuBuilder`, `ModalBuilder`,
#   `SlashCommandBuilder` from `@discordjs/builders`,
#   `REST` from `@discordjs/rest`, `WebSocketManager` from
#   `@discordjs/ws`, the `Collection` map subclass, and the
#   complete Discord Gateway v10 + Discord API v10 typed event
#   pipeline.  commandkit's `packages/commandkit/src/app/router.
#   ts` constructs typed `discord.js` `Client` instances,
#   registers `Events.InteractionCreate` /
